    provenianzaSource: (f) => '↳ inspired by: ' + f,
    principiTitle: '📜 PerTe\'s principles',
    principiIntro: 'PerTe is a space of <strong>safekeeping</strong> for memories. We don\'t invent stories: we receive them, respect them, and give them back to you. These are our commitments to you:',
    p1: '<strong>1. The story belongs to you.</strong> We don\'t invent events, people or details that don\'t come from your account. If a piece of information isn\'t there, we don\'t add it.',
    p2: '<strong>2. Better to omit than to invent.</strong> When we don\'t have enough to go on, we prefer silence over invention. A short, true letter is worth more than a long, false one.',
    p3: '<strong>3. The meaning doesn\'t change.</strong> If your memory was joy, it stays joy. If it was gratitude, it stays gratitude. We don\'t alter the meaning of what you felt.',
    p4: '<strong>4. We try to respect how you tell your story.</strong> If you speak simply, the letter will be simple. If you have humor, we try to keep it. We don\'t always succeed: if a sentence doesn\'t sound like you, you can delete it or tell us, and we\'ll redo it.',
    p5: '<strong>5. The form can change, the meaning cannot.</strong> We can reorder, connect, remove repetitions. But we don\'t change the heart of what you said.',
